               <p>JOHN LIGHTFOOT. I saw the prisoner take these things from my master's door; I followed him, and called stop thief. When he had got between thirty and forty yards, he dropped the things; I passed over them, and went on, and seized him; and I brought him and the property back.</p>

               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>

